22/06/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Interior Minister Ivica Dacic confirmed on Monday (June 21st) that there was cause to raise the level of security during his weekend visit to Republika Srpska (RS). 
He declined to elaborate or to comment on reports of a threat made against him. 
Some allege that associates of suspected drug trafficker Darko Saric planned to attack Dacic in Banja Luka. 
The RS Interior Ministry says only that police had questioned two people a day before the visit. 
(RTS, Tanjug, B92 - 21/06/10)
